{"key":"processedPost-19345699","value":{"id":19345699,"first":19342794,"last":19347569,"when":1388423768,"utime":"12/30/13 07:16 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>WillSolvem said:</strong><br />@RR the blowout plug will depressurize the vessel safely if left to fail</blockquote><br />For the record, that depends on the BTU rating of your stove.&nbsp; The blowout plug has a fairly small opening and can only release so much steam.&nbsp; In addition, they're made from rubber which tends to get stiff and brittle over time. Yours should have blown before the gauge read 30 lbs. <br />There should always be at least two means of overpressure control in the event that one of them fails. My 55 gallon drum boiler has three means of overpressure control for added safety.<br />RR"}}